WEEKEND DIGEST: BEVERLY HILLS; 
ADULT SCHOOL REGISTRATION 
Registration is under way for art, cooking, foreign language, writing and other 
classes in the Beverly Hills Adult School's fall term, which begins Sept. 10. 
The 174 classes, offered during the day and in the evening, include computer, 
business, health and social science courses, as well as traffic school, English 
as a Second Language and citizenship classes. The courses are open to all 
adults. 
Students may register by mail or by going to the adult education office, 255 
South Lasky Drive, from 8 a.m. to noon and 1 to 4:30 p.m., Monday through 
Friday. For more information, call 277-4747. 
